source.Name: Total population
source.Summary: Population: Total population and distribution by age and sex estimated to be consistent with the population by age and sex of the (a) 1946, 1951, 1956, 1961, 1966, 1971, 1979, 1981, 1986, 1991, 1996, 2002, 2006, 2011, 2016 censuses; (b) official estimates through 2022; (c) International estimates used up to 2019; and with estimates of the subsequent trends in fertility, mortality and international migration.

source.Name: Total fertility rate
source.Summary: Fertility: Total fertility rate and age pattern of fertility based on: (a) official estimates of age-specific fertility rates through 2021; (b) registered births classified by age of mother and the underlying female population by age through 2022; (c) adjusted for underregistration; (d) indirect estimates obtained using regression method with data on children ever born by age of mother from the 1945-2021 Estimates; (e) International estimates used up to 2019. In addition, the (a) births in the household in the preceding 12 (or 24) months classified by age of mother from the 2011 Census; (b) indirect estimates obtained from the application of the reverse survival method to the 1951, 1956, 1961, 1966, 1971, 1979, 1981, 1986, 1991, 1996, 2002, 2006, 2011, 2016 censuses and 1961-2011 Education Stats; (c) cohort-completed fertility backdated by the mean age of childbearing from the 1961, 1971, 2006, 2011, 2016 censuses have been considered.

source.Name: Life expectancy at birth
source.Summary: Overall Mortality: Life expectancy at birth and age pattern of mortality based on: (a) official estimates through 2017; (b) registered deaths by age and sex available through 2021; (c) International estimates used up to 2021.

source.Name: Infant/child mortality
source.Summary: Child Mortality: Under-five mortality based on: (a) official estimates of infant and child mortality through 2017; (b) registered infant and child deaths through 2021.

source.Name: International migration
source.Summary: Migration: International migration based on: (a) official figures of net international migration flows, and assumed subsequent trends in international migration; (b) estimates of migrant flows, and assumed subsequent trends in international migration; (c) information on foreign-born populations from censuses and registers from major countries of destination; (d) estimates derived as the differences between overall population growth and natural increase; (e) UNHCR statistics on the number of refugees in the main countries of asylum.
